The requirement that the rehearing be heard as if the proceedings had no been dealt with in the arbitration prevents any use being made of the evidence in, or the course of the, proceedings before the arbitrator, unless that material is tendered by consent: Courtenay v Proprietors Strata Plan No 12125  (NSWCA, Priestley, Sheller, Beazley JJA, CA 40599/96, 30 October 1998, unreported, BC9807357); Najdanovic v Brown (t/as Taylor's A1 Transport Co)  (NSWSC, Finlay J, CLD 15136/82, 22 September 1992, unreported, BC9203158), reproduced behind “Practice Decisions” at 
[190,225]
).
